-atlassian","html_url":"https://github.com/scaldwell-atlassian","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/scaldwell-atlassian/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/scaldwell-atlassian/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/scaldwell-atlassian/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/scaldwell-atlassian/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/scaldwell-atlassian/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/scaldwell-atlassian/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/scaldwell-atlassian/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/scaldwell-atlassian/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/scaldwell-atlassian/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2018-07-24T03:31:00Z","updated_at":"2018-07-24T18:36:51Z","body":"So...after playing around a bit, I found the following workaround.  In my case I have two VMs spun up from the same Vagrantfile, both mount /vagrant.  To do this and persist across reboots, I did this: \r\n\r\n\r\ntarget.vm.synced_folder \"share/proxyTarget\", \"/vagrant\"\r\nconfig.vm.provision :shell, inline: <<-SHELL\r\n    set -e\r\n    ### Redacted ###\r\n    echo \"vboxsf\" >> /etc/modules\r\n    echo \"vagrant /vagrant vboxsf defaults 0 0\" >> /etc/fstab\r\n    mount -t vboxsf vagrant /vagrant\r\n    ### Redacted ###\r\nSHELL\r\n\r\n\r\n(Thanks to the person who pinged me side channel to ask for a better explanation to my workaround.)","author_association":"NONE","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/hashicorp/vagrant/issues/comments/407269330/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":null,"event":"commented","actor":{"login":"scaldwell-atlassian","id":41401213,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjQxNDAxMjEz","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubuserconten